Dialog: I DON'T HAVE AN UMBRELLA WITH ME.
MAYBE YOU WANT TO WAIT TILL THE RAIN STOPS.
I SAW YOU TRYING TO WALK IN THE RAIN JUST THEN.
I- YEAH- (BITTERLY) I DIDN'T MEAN IT.
THE RAIN IS TOO HEAVY YOU CAN'T GO LIKE THIS.
I KNOW- BUT I DON'T HAVE ONE WITH ME
TRY SEE IF ANYONE CAN TAKE YOU.
YEAH. WELL- ARE YOU WAITING FOR SOMEONE IN HERE?
I’M HEADING BACK SOON. GOTTA FINISH MY CIGARETTE.
OH- SURE. HOPE YOU DON’T MIND.  I’M JUST CURIOUS.
I KNOW IT MAY SEEM WEIRD. BUT …
NOTHING- I’M KINDA- JUST ENJOYING THE RAIN. BYE.
EXCUSE ME- CAN I WALK WITH YOU?
I DON‘T HAVE AN UMBRELLA WITH ME
OH- HI. ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME?
I’M KIDDING. NO WORRIES. I RECOGNIZE YOU- I THINK WE LIVED IN THE SAME NEIGHBORHOOD.
YOU LOOK FAMILIAR TO ME TOO. BUT I DONT THINK I VE SEEN YOU.  JUST FAMILIAR.
I SAW YOU DON'T HAVE AN UMBRELLA. AND WE LIVE CLOSE. I THINK WE CAN GO TOGETHER.
Whether the sky is sad or not.
What kind of music do you like?
**RAIN** I LIKE the song have a 'rain' in its name.
Here you are. my music player.
